A new-born baby boy was found at the front door of a house in the Dube area in Soweto on Sunday morning, ER24 said in a statement. "ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at 07:34 to find several bystanders nearby. On closer inspection, medics found a new-born baby boy with a member of the public," spokesperson Russel Meiring said. The baby boy had no injuries but was transported to a nearby hospital for further medical attention. "It is understood that the new-born had been left at the front door of a residence," Meiring explained. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.